	"description": "Imagine you have an e-commerce website and you’re allowing users to create\naccounts using their name and email. You want to make sure they sign up with\nreal names, not something like cool_dud3.\n\nThat&#x27;s where we use validation to validate inputs and make sure input data\nfollows certain rules.\n\nIn the market, we already have a bunch of validation libraries, but I will\ncompare two important validation libraries: Joi [https://github.com/hapijs/joi] \nand express-validator [https://github.com/express-",
